{"title": "Opticks", "description": "The famous physicist Sir Isaac Newton lectured on optics from 1670 - 1672. He worked on refraction of light into colored beams using prisms and discovered chromatic aberration. He also postulated the corpuscular form of light and an ether to transmit forces between the corpuscles. His \"Opticks\", first published 1704 contains his postulates about the topic. This is the fourth edition in English, from 1730, which Newton himself had corrected from the third edition before his death. (Summary by Availle)", "duration": 43979, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2836", "name": "Sir Isaac Newton"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt21/opticks_1207.jpg", "copyright_year": "1730", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Nature", "Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Rapunzelina"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Titlepage and Advertisements", "readers": [4174], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/opticks_1203_librivox/opticks_00_newton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 333}, {"section": 1, "title": "Book I Part I - Definitions", "readers": [7065], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/opticks_1203_librivox/opticks_01_newton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 380}, {"section": 2, "title": "Book I Part I - Axioms", "readers": [4174], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/opticks_1203_librivox/opticks_02_newton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1409}, {"section": 3, "title": "Book I Part I - Proposition I", "readers": [6749], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/opticks_1203_librivox/opticks_03_newton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 692}, {"section": 4, "title": "Book I Part I - Proposition II, Section 1", "readers": [3698], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/opticks_1203_librivox/opticks_04_newton_64kb.mp3", "duration": 745}, {"section": 5, "title": "Book